      "weather": "FINE",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKI ALMIGHTY (5) made a good start to his career two-and-a-half weeks ago, beaten 4 metres into third over 1740m at this track. Stepping up a level this time but he is better for that last hit-out and capable of opening his account. BETTOR INTHE DARK (9) stayed out of the early speed battle from a wide gate on the front line last start and was never in the race, finishing 17 metres from the winner in seventh here over 2270m. Drawn to enjoy an economical run and might sweat on the sprint lane. Meets a similar quality field and is good enough to take out a race like this. A CLASS APART (3) is a three-year-old gelding by Tintin In America from African Dancer on debut. Has the benefit of a good draw. Placed in a recent trial and looks well-placed to score at his first appearance. KYCORDEN (8) must be considered after he finished third over 1720m at Young a week ago. One for the exotics players.",
